                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-600 uppercase">Avg Waterproofing Cost</span>
                <span class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-900">$12,000-$25,000</span>
              </li>
                <li class="flex justify-between items-center pb-2 border-b border-slate-100">
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-600 uppercase">Flood Risk</span>
                <span class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-900">RAVINE + BLUFF EROSION</span>
              </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-navy-900 border-2 border-slate-200 p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 uppercase">WHY SCARBOROUGH NEEDS BASEMENT WATERPROOFING</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300">
                <li class="text-sm text-slate-300 flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-2 text-cyan-400">•</span>
                <span>Glacial bluff clay creates unstable, moisture-retaining soil</span>
              </li>
                <li class="text-sm text-slate-300 flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-2 text-cyan-400">•</span>
                <span>Bluffs and ravines create highly variable water tables</span>
              </li>
                <li class="text-sm text-slate-300 flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-2 text-cyan-400">•</span>
                <span>860mm+ annual rainfall plus lake-effect storms</span>
              </li>
                <li class="text-sm text-slate-300 flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-2 text-cyan-400">•</span>
                <span>Highland Creek and Rouge River seasonal flooding</span>
              </li>
                <li class="text-sm text-slate-300 flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-2 text-cyan-400">•</span>
                <span>Freeze-thaw cycles crack aging foundations</span>
              </li>
                <li class="text-sm text-slate-300 flex items-start">
                <span class="mr-2 text-cyan-400">•</span>
                <span>1950s-80s homes reaching end-of-life on original drainage</span>
              </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

